result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (3rd) and Operating w/ PAC (3rd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (3rd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (3rd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Blaine Scott Rosek was found guilty of OWI (3rd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Blaine Scott Rosek was found guilty of Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

ADDRESS INFO for Blaine Scott Rosek
Current: 744 Eagle Lane, Wabeno, WI 54566 United States  (Effective: 09-21-2015)
Prior: 5363 Linden Street, Laona, WI 54541

Defendant Blaine Scott Rosek in court with attorney Brian F. Bennett.  Defendant Blaine Scott Rosek in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Called at 8:48 AM. Called 16CF86, 15CF144 and 15CM159. State - all matters are resolved. State - 15CM159 - plead g/nc to count #1 with prior acknowledgement of 2 prior convictions - joint of 60 days jail, $1900.00 fine, 24 month DL revocation, 24 month IID, #2 - dismissed, #3 - plead as alleged with court costs only; 16CF86 - #2 - DRI, #1 - joint recommendation of costs only and 45 days jail - consecutive to 15CM159 jail time with huber and good time; 15CF144 - have complied with victim notification requirements with no response - g/nc to counts #1 and #4 as alleged, #2 and #3 - DRI, free to argue for sentencing on that matter and State will be asking for 2 years probation but Bennett is free to argue. Bennett and Rosek agree and have provided the Court with plea questionnaires. Court - 15CF144 - dismisses and reads in counts #2 and #3, Rosek pleads G to counts #1 and #4; 15CM159 - #2 - dismissed, Rosek pleads G to count #1 as alleged and #3 as alleged; 16CF86 - #2 - DRI, Rosek plead G to count #1 as alleged. Rosek acknowledges two prior OWI convictions. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - will not state anything further on the joint recommendation cases but will make argument on 15CF144 - asking for the defendant to be placed on probation for 2 years with conditions of: AODA and anger management with follow thru, no alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, FT employment/school, 150 hours of community service, no affiliation with Ivan Milham, otherwise follow joint recommendation on other matters. Bennett makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation on 15CM159 and 16CF86 and makes argument for sentence on 15CF144 - recommends probation as well but leaves the amount of time up to the Court - credit for the time as stated by defense and ask for the money posted in 15CF144 to be returned to the poster, would like a condition of no contact with Travis Bird, informs Court that the defendant has never been placed on probation before. Rosek makes statement, remorseful. Court sentences the defendant to the following: 15CM159 - 60 days in FC jail - huber and good time allowed - eligible for community service under 973.03(3), $1900 fine - paid at rate of $50.00/month commencing 1st month following release from custody, 2 year DL revocation, IID for 2 years on DL and any vehicle titled in his name commencing upon issuance of valid DL, count #3 - costs only - paid paid at rate of $50.00/month commencing 1st month following release from custody; 16CF86 - count #1 - costs - paid paid at rate of $50.00/month commencing 1st month following release from custody, 45 days in FC jail - consecutive to jail time on 15CM159 - huber and good time allowed - eligible for community service under 973.03(3) - credit for 3 days; 15CF144 - counts #1 and #4 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 2 years, concurrent to each other and concurrent to jail terms on 15CM159 and 16CF86, with conditions of: AODA and follow thru, anger management and follow thru, costs - take bond posted and any remainder can be put on other cases, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, 150 hours of community service, no contact with Ivan Milham or Travis Bird, no consumption or possession of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, credit for 38 days only if revoked (stipulated), submit DNA sample, right to appeal, adjourned.
